==Scottish Gaelic==

===Etymology===
Early Irish [[cráeb]], [[cróeb]]

===Noun===
'''craobh'''  {{f}}, '''craobhan''' {{p}}

# [[tree]], [[bush]]
# [[relation]]
# ear of oats (craobh coirce)
# streaming clouds, rising from the horizon and spreading wide as they ascend to the zenith
# foam or globules on the surface of liquids
# [[richness]]

===Verb===
'''craobh'''

#[[spread]]
#gush out and [[ramify]] at the same time
#* fhuil a' craobhadh mu thalamh
#** his blood gushing and ramifying
#[[propagate]], shoot forth
#branch out, [[sprout]], [[bud]]

